caption: Decided to try this place, instead of my usual favorite bbq place next door...Spiced Right.  Big mistake!  Food didn't taste fresh and was no where near the quality and taste you get from Spiced Right.  Service was OK, but it was pretty empty at the time.  Stay with the tried and true,  Lesson learned.  Won't be back.
Nothing like the pictures worst time I ever spent money

Service was great. But the food was not really good at all. I got the brisket sandwich and the cheddar sausage sandwich. I'm not sure either would qualify as bbq as they tasted like they came from a freezer and definitely weren't smoked. The fries were very below average as well and the bbq sauce tasted like it came from the generic aisle of the grocery store.
Wings were amazing. This place is great! Also has a sweet deck.

We found our barbecue spot! First of all the food was fresh, hot, and absolutely delicious. If you're looking for something different, this is the spot. The staff were friendly and welcoming. Outstanding ambiance for a relaxing place to kick back and dine. We had the brisket burger and the Mac and cheese pulled pork burger-both were bomb...not to mention that they had a ton of unique options on the menu that we can't wait to try like their bbq tacos, bbq nachos, and more. We will be back again and again. Outside seating and pet-friendly. Thanks for a great evening guys!  ~Bobby, Jen, and Hazey-Dog
Disappointing; first time was great, second and third not so much, the food was pretty mediocre, better customer service is needed as well
Food was tasteless

Good service; in general food was ok;good fried okra;  this is not a regular BBQ place, it is pulled brisket very dry; heard the Burria is good; Turn on the heat; place was freezing; No ice tea in a bbq joint?? Place was empty which is not usually a good sign...

Recently, learned about Birria from Eater website, which is a combination smoking/braising technique for brisket,  so we had to seek some out. This place is at a great location in Roswell with a great patio. In March, they will have live music on Friday nights. Also, expect beer and wine to be joining the menu. The Birria Tacos came with a bowl of the sauce used in braising for dipping. The tacos had just enough crunch with good flavor, plenty of meat and very filling. The Birria nachos were big enough to share. Plenty of meat and great presentation; although, I would have liked more jalapenos. But that is a me thing...never enough jalapenos. I highly recommend and I look forward to coming back for the great patio when it is warmer.
Really Good. My son got the chicken tenders and fried okra. The chicken was juicy and the okra crispy. I got the burger with macncheese, both also delicious.
Good food with reasonable prices but beer pitcher terribly expensive, bad music
Dry hamburgers but good music on the deck.
Great atmosphere, food and music! I'll be back.
Love this place! Delicious food, great vibes, love music, just the way I like it. Highly recommend the deep fried pies, phenomenal
Great Food cool staff soul food in Roswell yum family environment small/ medium dogs welcome Shout out to the entire staff excellent service
Love this place

Small unsuspecting restaurant that has a great consistency rating of great atmosphere with live music on wkends, great food.. even in the mist of this COVID 19 pandemic, and the best customer interaction with owner, wait staff and chef. Together it made celebrating our anniversary very special..
As always, a great meal with fantastic staff and chef. Keep up the great service. Cheers!
Love this place!

Hidden Gem! I must try this place for Dinner, as well. We stumbled upon this place after hiking in Roswell. Lucky we did. Jacquelyn was awesome! Very knowledgeable of the menu and personable. The food options were so cool. We got a ton of appetizers as well as the Fish and grits. The sauce was amazing! Glad to see this place thriving. The outside patio was awesome. If I lived a little closer I would be back weekly! The dinner menu and the dinner specials are a must try for the next go around.

First visit last year was not good, but the atmophere, menu and prices have changed for the better.  It's a simpler menu, prices are much more reasonable and portions are generous.  Most importantly, the food tastes really good and fresh.  Waitress was excellent, drinks are good and the patio was alot of fun for a larger group like ours.  I could definitely see coming back more often.
Excellent service, friendly staff, very clean and the catfish was incredible. Must go!
Sweet fried green tomatoes.  Unbelievable.

This restaurant is amazing. The owners are so gracious and go out of their way to make you welcomed. My grandkids and I ( I'm visiting from Wisconsin) was on our third stop to get something to eat. We were there before they were actually opened and they allowed us to order anyway. The food was great but the memory they made for us was a blessing.

Our 2nd time to Chippers, the first was Pre COVID back in February which we thoroughly enjoyed.  Food, Music and friendly atmosphere. My husband and I drove by after a hike  yesterday, Sunday, and debated about take out or open seating on patio.  At 11:30am we saw there weren't  many people, waitstaff were wearing masks, we felt the tables were adequately socially distanced, and the singer/songwriter was fabulous.  So - wearing our masks (wanting to also protect waitstaff and others before receiving our food) we sat down.  Unfortunately the proprietor was mingling freely within a couple feet of his patrons, including us,  without a mask.  Our Governor' mandates masks and other precautions  for restaurants in his 40 page Executive Order which I read after our experience. Enough said.  Shrimp and Grits were quite good - but unfortunately we won't be going back.  Counting 14 days... Not following guidelines is a dangerous game for patrons, employees and for the economy.
Great place all around for food and service and music.  Try it.
Great neighborhood hang out!

Super super friendly owners and staff quaint atmosphere awesome huge patio I can't wait to come in the spring to listen to music and drink wine. They had live music last Saturday which was quite good also we double-dated and our food was great and the other couple seemed very pleased with theirs as well. They let me taste a couple of wines and I just thought everything was fabulous!
Reuben sandwich for lunch was great
Good food and service. We'll be back!

Had an amazing meal at Chipper's. Carl took care of us and showed us an awesome time. The hospitality at this place is great. Every course was excellent. In particular, the Chocolate Banana Bread Pudding blew us away. Really solid drink selection too. Highly recommended. We will definitely be back.

My mini me and I came across this place one night and decided to stop by and show them some love. When we walked in, it wasn't too crowded, and we were greeted immediately by the staff. The made us feel at home and offered us any seat in the house. We chose to sit near the back as there was live music being played in the front of the restaurant. Nicole took care of us once we were seated. Now Nicole and I had this love hate relationship. Why you ask... because she proceeds to tell us that she did not like sports, but she was a newfound New Orleans "AINTS" fan! I immediately asked to be moved to another section. I kid..I kid... It was all in good fun as Atlanta and New Orleans are big rivals.  Despite Nicole being a fan of that other team... she took very good care of us. She recommended the Southern Egg Rolls, The Swiss Bacon Mushroom Burger and the Shrimp and Grits. While I hate to give anybody, who roots for that team any credit... Nicole was spot on. The food was phenomenal.  The egg rolls where certainly something I had never had before... They had apple wood smoked pork as the meat with BBQ sauce and slaw on the side.  The burger while cooked to perfection and seasoned well... it didn't have anything on that Shrimp & Grits dish! Let me tell you... I'm a Fat A$$ and I love food and I will admit this without hesitation. This Shrimp & Grits was the best I've had so far. This DISH gave me LIFE. All the flavors were perfect and the HEAT (Spices that is) was on point. I certainly will go back to have this dish again. Compliments to the chef!  On my next visit I will also try the Rib Eye... that was my mom's favorite cut of meat and now its mines. I was eyeballing the Rib Eye on another plate.  I highly encourage you all to pay them a visit. If you are a Falcon's Fan... avoid Nicole's section! I'm just kidding. You all won't be disappointed in this establishment.  If you stop by... tell'em Drew sent ya! Y'all Be Easy! Drew

My friends and I have a great dinner at Chippers every time we go there.  I highly recommend you try their desserts.   Best wine selection in Roswell area.   Great job.
Good food and fun place.

Great, surprise.  Small restaurant but it had live music, good food, and friendly staff.  Food cost a little more than I expected but tasted good.  I like the smoked wings the best.  The weather was cold and rainy but the patio looked really fun if the weather was nicer.  Really enjoyed the guitarist they had playing!

We went because there was a coupon in the Dining Out book. But what a pleasant surprise to find a varied cocktail menu, inventive and well prepared dishes, all served on a lovely, dog-friendly patio (where the staff all came to visit my delighted pup!) We both had excellent seafood dishes. We will be back!

First visit with a group of friends yesterday. The place was cozy and inviting, like having a dinner party at a friend's house. The staff was very friendly and attentive. The food was fresh and full of flavor. We were just visiting so it's a bit out of the way for us but will visit again if we're ever in the area.
Service was great. Food was ok..
A group of us came in and we were met with excellent, quick service. The food is great to boot. Loved the sweet potato fries!
Great Food . Great Owner

We had an excellent time at Chipper's last night. One of the owners greeted us at the door and was very hospitable. Our waiter, Cindy, was attentive and friendly. But most of all the food was delicious! I had the Shrimp n' Grits and loved them.
Delicious food and excellent customer service

Small local restaurant with great food. Walking up,  I wasn't impressed with the outside,  but looks aren't everything! The inside was clean and charming. I ordered the avocado, tomato,  and pecans arugula salad and added the sesame crusted seared tuna. The homemade avocado dressing was the perfect complement to the flavors. I'll go back for sure.
The wings were cold and really don't have much taste to me
Cute establishment!! Super friendly service! Caitlin was super sweet and food was delicious. Coming back for live music and relaxing on the patio!!
Great food and atmosphere with live music and Johnny our waiter was fantastic

Went here this evening. The food was amazing!  We had halibut dinner and shrimp and scallop diner. Great - fabulous service. Great music and friendly and knowledgeable  servers. Definitely a be back place

I ate here this week and was super impressed with every aspect of this restaurant. Good ambiance, great service and great food. We had the fried chicken and shrimp and grits and both were amazing. Our waitress was awesome and owner was there and stopped by our table to make sure everything was good. We will be back soon!
Great cocktails. Awesome appetizers. Can't wait to try dinner.
Food wasn’t what I expected, prices are to high and the servers were not to very attending. On top of that my food took about 50 min to come out, I just wouldn’t come back
I love the food and the service! 👍

This place is a real gem. Great outdoor patio, live music and just happens to have amazing food. What I love is that it's every bit as good (if not better) as the restaurants on Canton Street in Roswell, but without the traffic or congestion.  Also, love their drink options!
We visited this restaurant for the first time. It was a pleasant surprise. Will definitely return.
Great food. Excellent service!

Great Food and Atmosphere! Carl and our waitress were so personable and the dishes were very good! OMG the steak dish I had was just awesome. Skirt steak melted in my mouth and the fancy small potatoes with the fire roasted red pepper relish with fresh rosemary was just to die for! Well worth the money for sure. I highly recommend this cozy but truly unforgettable place. One of the best steak dishes I've had so far (sorry, picture does not show much of the steak as I devoured it before I took the photo)
Great food great service super friendly staff

Food was good.  My friend's burger was no different than any other restaurant.  Prices are too high for the amount of food you get.  Our server wasn't very attentive.  Went long periods of time without seeing her and the restaurant was fairly empty.  The owner is very nice, she tried  to make up for the server's shortcomings.

I really enjoyed ambiance this restaurant. Had the catfish over grits, while not much of a catfish person I thoroughly enjoyed it. My friend had the Sweet/Hot Fried Chicken and that was delicious as well. The owner was very nice and made us feel like we were part of the family. There was live entertainment there as well, and that guy needs a record deal, he was super good.  I love finding hidden gems like this in my neighborhood. I would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking for a good meal..
Great food, customer service and atmosphere.
sneaky good! owner is very nice and proud of his business. give it a shot!
Very good food lots of fresh ingredients

My girlfriend and I ate at Chipper's last night.  When we walked in, we were greeted by the owner, waitress and even the chef.  They were friendly and just a great group of people to enjoy hanging out with.  And, the real reason we went there was for the food.  The food was outstanding!  If you haven't tried them, it's a must!  You won't regret it.  We'll be regulars.

My friend and I celebrated our birthdays at Chipper's Club and had a fabulous time! The owner, Carl Thompson, Chef Horton and our servers were very welcoming and accommodating. The food was absolutely delicious! We will definitely go back again and again.

This is great neighborhood spot with a great patio. (Yes there is road noise but great music Thursday-sat helps drown that out. The food is good, the shrimp and grits is true Louisiana style.  I’ll be back will the fam! Hey kids eat free Tuesday-Thursday!!

Great food, convenient location, nice staff. Kids eat free Tues-Thurs. I came here with a group of mom's with kids. Three of them got there first and ordered and were served promptly. Me and another got there later and had to wait a long time, even though we only ordered sandwiches. That being said, the staff were friendly and apologetic. They had a couple of big groups come in at the same time as us which was the reason for the delay. We ate outside on the patio and the staff were friendly and welcoming to our kiddos playing and dancing to the music. The food was good quality and prepared with care. The parking was a bit cramped, but ok. Worth checking out of your in the area.
Great food is guaranteed no matter what you order. Weekend Music on the patio.
Great time... Great ownership... Food was great! Really unique and tasty shrimp and grits... Probably best I've ever had or damn near close! The pork rolls are amazing too. Will be back
Great food and service.   The Hot Chicken sandwich was quite unique with mac n cheese.   A definite place to visit again.
Very good place to have a real Martinis drinks🍸
No better place to have lunch or dinner! Food is great and service is always welcoming! Family owned restaurant that is personable! Carl and his wife are great and always great to talk too!
Chippers have an awesome menu and the waitress is attentive. The mananger is very personable! Food is excellent!
We were out running errands today with our pup and decided to stop by Chipper's for lunch. The food and service were both outstanding. I highly recommend giving them a try.
Service food ambience equals the triple threat.
Great food, service, location. Great live music - a solo vocalist who is awesome. Chef was gracious and visited every table. Owner (Chipper) also came with his kids and ate ..... that's a good sign.

The food and service was mediocre and I actually had to send back my fried chicken because it was pink inside. Drink specials on Tues. and Thurs. are decent. I really wanted this place to compete with downtown Roswell’s restaurants but there is no contest!
Great food, friendly staff, what's not to love?
Great food. Will go back soon.
Great place to get a great tasting and fresh meal. We had the shrimp and grits and they were amazing. Our waiter was attentive and nice. Great patio to seat in too.

Stopped in for an early dinner- great choices, yummy food amd friendly, fast service. We ordered the deviled eggs which were great.  I had the pulled pork BBQ sandwich w/ parmsean fries, husband had the fried chicken salad sandwich and sweet potato fries- both delicious.  Will be back!

The menu looked amazing and the service was great, but I was disappointed in the food. We ordered their Chorizo Mac n Cheese and the stuffed Chorizo Meatloaf. Both agreed that it wasn't did not chorizo. There wasn't much flavor to it at all. The mac n cheese while good was not great. It wasn't very cheesy and the chorizo tasted like ground beef. It was eh. While looking at other's peoples food. The salmon looked small, but the Korean noodles and fried green tomatoes looked very good
Great food and great service. Nice folks, too.
You must go! Live entertainment great food service is exemplar! I mean exemplar!We'll be back! Heart of Roswell.

Food was expensive and the portion size was small. I had the spicy chicken sandwich which was good but again it was small and it cost $13. The chips that came with the sandwich were stale. personally I would never go back because I don't like spending that much for lunch

Disappointed by this location, the service, and the food portions. Located south of Downtown Roswell, and next to a noisy roadway, this establishment serves New Orleans seafood and cuisine. They have a spacious patio, and although their food may be good, the portions leave much to be desired.  It took absolutely forever for us to get our order - a beer and a couple appetizers, and when it arrived, we were disappointed. It seems trendy to up charge on appetizers to set the expectation for the entrees. After reviewing the options, I would have chosen a steakhouse as they would have offered more seafood options and a better atmosphere. All the bet to this restaurant and its owner, but I won't be heading back.
Small business with great food and hospitable owners. I love going here
The food is excellent. I wanted to order every dish on the menu. Service was excellent as well
Great location. Super friendly bartender Nikki and manager Matt.   Great deck
Great service, nice patio day
Five stars for sure.  Very good food and awesome staff.    The owner personally introduced himself and thanked us for coming.  Will be back for sure

This is an amazing dining establishment.  The owner is as active and attentive as the wait staff who are all also very attentive and amazing.  They are not afraid to come over and spend some extra time with you and joke with you and make plenty of suggestions on the menu items.  This is a warm and inviting place and probably the first place I have been to that understands that live music should be part of the background and not take over the entire place.   Their drink selection was on point and my meal (Steak with Garlic Potatoes) was amazing.  My fiancee got the Salmon and I was told it was just as amazing.  Go ahead and save room for dessert it is worth the extra money.  their dessert menu is impressive.  I had gotten something to share with my fiancee but next time I will be getting my own, There was plenty to share but it was so good I think next time I won't want to.  I was told they have an entirely different menu for lunches so I am definitely making it a point to go back for lunch one day in the near future hopefully when it is warm enough to use the amazing patio space they have. I highly recommend this place to everyone that is thinking about eating in Roswell.

We had nice weather so we ate on the patio.  The food was not really my favorite but that is just a matter of taste as it was prepared as explained.  They get an extra star for having live music which was great!
Just a great place for Dinner!  Food is unique and delicious, service is great and environment is fun to sit on the deck and enjoy the music!
Best Food and Awesome Service.  Best People in Roswell

4 of us went for dinner and it was the second time for 2 in the party.  I never review restaurants, but everyone had something different plus two appetizers shared and all was fantastic. My main reason for leaving the review is because I had the fried chicken with a "spicy glaze" on it and it totally reminded me of the awesome (Late Roswell restaurant ) Greenwoods' fried chicken that set my bar.  This was as good or better.  Going back!

Just got done eating here and I gotta tell you it's one of the best places I've eaten at in Atlanta. So good infact that I forgot to snap a picture of the sandwich - Chattahoochee Sweet & Hot Friend Chicken with Paramesan Fries. Highly recommend trying it out and I'll definitely be back. It's worth the drive!
Great people great service great environment
Great dinner and lunch loved our server Nicky an the manger Matt was awesome an helpful, will definitely be back here

Very good dishes. We had the fried catfish w/grits and the chorizo stuffed meatloaf. They were both excellent. Not impressed with the deviled eggs. Nice presentation but lacked taste...very bland. Owner (Carl) personally made rounds to each of the tables and was very nice. Offers 20% discount on food for teachers/educators. Nice touch!!
The BEST team, the BEST food and the BEST (dog friendly!) Patio!! Will be returning!!! Thank you, Carl, for showing my family an amazing time!

Great food!  Enjoyed eating out on the deck on a beautiful day.  The owner Carl took the time to talk to every table on the deck.  Made us feel right at home.  I loved that I was able to bring my dog and that the waitress brought the dog a bowl of water without even being asked.  My burger was top notch.  Can't wait to go back.  I recommended the place to 5 friends already.
Awesome place.  Food was great.  Will definately come back.
Good food. Fun experience.
Amazing sandwiches! Would come back and recommend to a friend. Waitress was awesome and Carl was funny and appreciative for our service. Can’t wait to see them again!
The BBQ sandwich was absolutely amazing so glad we stopped in
Great food.
They let my 4 year old nephew use the bathroom. Thx!
Too pricey.  C'mon man.

Stopped in to Chippers for lunch on New Year's Day with my family. Menu was full of great options. Staff was friendly and owner stopped by and had a great conversation. You could tell everything was made fresh. Even kids fruit was freshly sliced berries. Will go again!

Currently my new favorite restaurant in Roswell! The food is amazinggggg and the service is even better. Been here a few times and always leave satisfied and happy. I would recommend they’re prime steak and goat cheese fritters for appetizer.

Ate there for the first time yesterday and loved it!  Service was great, the place is comfortable and the food is wonderful.  (I think the fried green tomatoes were some of the best I ever had!)  Carl, the owner was delightful and he has done a great job of making his place comfortable and enjoyable.  Great neighborhood addition!
Amazing food and amazing staff!

Tried this place today for lunch with my daughter because we were looking for something new. Loved it! Our waitress, Nicky, was extremely nice and helpful with suggestions of what to try. We had the southern egg rolls, shrimp and grits and a salad topped with salmon. We met one of the owners, Carl, and he promised we would be very pleased with the food. He was so right! Loved everything and we will definitely be returning very soon.
Came here for brunch and to see 🎅.  Our family loved the food and atmosphere.  Definitely will be back soon!

Went here for a late lunch and was met by Carl (owner) who seated us and guided us through the menu.  He is passionate about his new place, and he should be.  We had the $15 pound of wings and 2 drafts, Southern  BBQ spring rolls, and fries.  The wings were amazing - smoked with a whiskey and creole mustard glaze - really, these wings are some of the best I've had.  They have a flavor profile that you usually don't associate with wings - pretty special.  The Southern Egg Rolls are a meal in themselves - smokey apple BBQ pork and some dipping sauce.  Didn't care for the coleslaw served with this dish - but I'm not a coleslaw guy.  The handmade fries were fresh out of the fryer and cooked to perfection.  The food will get me to come back and Carl and his staff make me feel like family.  Give Chipper's Club a try - you'll come back again if you do.
Very nice environment and food was great

One of the rare new gems in Roswell Welcoming staff, casual atmosphere with upscale cusine , the patio offers live music and TV inside and out let's you get your sports on too. Fried Green Tomatoes, Roasted Chicken with vegetable, and a Nutella brownie for dessert. Yum
Family loved it!
Delicious food and great service!

Went there with my family on Friday night. The Goat cheese fritters were amazing. I had the meatloaf and my husband had the catfish and grits. We both loved our meals. My daughter loved her sandwich and fruit cup. First time she has ever finished a meal at a restaurant  And the staff was incredible. Love the atmosphere.

My fiancee discovered this place tonight while I was getting my haircut and I must say that I am very glad that she did.  After speaking with the server I found out that the joint opened up 3 months ago.  There were a lot of enticing things on the menu, but you should try the Chattahoochee Sweet & Spicy fried chicken... You'll thank me later.  Exactly as its name suggests - it starts out sweet, almost with a honey taste and ends with a spiciness, but not overpowering.  The chicken was fresh and well cooked ... It's making me hungry just writing about it.  You should definitely grab a table on the patio on a Thursday, Friday, or Saturday evening; enjoy some live music; and eat some delicious food.

Excellent service, loved the menu choices. The place has had a complete facelift.  Had a couple appetizers and split for quick lunch.  We can not wait to come back and try dinner.  Chef and Owner both came by and spoke with us. Wonderful experience !!
Food was great, nice music, great atmosphere

Went there last weekend for dinner- our first time.  Everyone from the hostess, to Chip and Karl and Nikki our waitress were so welcoming.  The food was outstanding!!  The deck is large, had great entertainment and is off the crowded path of all the other Roswell restaurants.  If you want a relaxing enjoyable and delicious meal and people who make you feel welcomed - then Chipper's Club is the place!!!
Friendly staff..  Great wings..
Good menu, great service and not crowded for a late lunch. Can't wait to go back and try more!
Food was excellent, a little mix up between the fried chicken and fried chicken sandwich but didn't change my perspective a bit hot and sweet was good...so was the catfish.

I requested a bowl to vomit into, and since the waitstaff thought I was joking they gave me one.   Once my seafood scallops came I puked in the bowl then poured it on my meal.  It was my birthday, and still is, so the staff cheered on the strongboy, Darrick, who holds the birthday boy's (or boy's) face into the vomitbowl while he performs the job.  Overall, a harrowing and delcious heart-n-soul event.
Fried chicken was out of bounds!!!
The dinner,  appetizer and dessert all excellent. They also had great music on the back deck Saturday night.
Lovely dinner out on the deck, listening to great live music!  Food was terrific and service was outstanding.  VERY happy to have such a great new restaurant so close to home.
It's the total package. Great food, great service, fun atmosphere. Relaxed casual dining. It's a must try.

We are actually at the restaurant right now. I’ve eaten all of my catfish and grits and I’m now finishing my wife’s massive plate of fried chicken. This place is exactly what Roswell needed. Traditional southern food that hasn’t been all twisted up by an overzealous chef.  Chippers nailed it. It’s just plain delicious and the staff is great. I’ll be coming back again and again. I have a feeling this place is going to become a Roswell staple.
Outstanding food and service.

Fantastic service, nicely presented plates, and tasty food. We had their Cobb Salad and Salmon dinner. The kids had grilled shrimp and peanut butter nutella sandwich. They have lots of gluten free options for our celiac daughter.
Lunch was awesome. Great food, great service!!
you can't beat the whole experience: atmosphere, service and food!

Fantastic menu...Best meal I've had all year! Chattahoochee Sweet and Hot Fried Chicken - unbeatable flavor, succulent chicken, with a little spicy zest calmed by sweet glaze with crust you won't believe! Must try dish.
A lovely addition to restaurant row in lovely Roswell. I highly recommend the catfish and grits with a side of mac and cheese of course.

Have passed by here as it was getting ready to open.  Pulled in to give it a try. Was not disappointed.  The place has a happy welcoming vibe.  They are glad you are here with out spoken words you can tell.   Having just read in the AJC  two lights to the south Moxie Burger was crowned as the best burger in Atlanta.  Thats serious stuff.  I ordered the burger.   It was good.. great.... fantastic  It was that good. Tasty, moist and nice size. With each bite I slowed down.  Can't wait to return and try the rest of the menu.  Not ready to leave we ordered the fired pie... I know, I know. Need it like a hole in the head. With a scoop of ice cream and a new spoon.  Smiled as I filled my pie hole. That stuff is yummy.

Great casual atmosphere with upscale menu. I had the catfish and grits with greens.Excellant, crisp on the ouside but very moist inside, great sauce. Nice wine selection.  Nice presentation. Great addition to the variety of restaurants on Canton Street. Enjoyed the meal and good service. It’s close to Oxbow Road, a little south of the crowded part of Canton. It has parking!! I highly recommend it. Thank you Carl. Glad you are here in Roswell!

The food was phenomenal. The roasted vegetables were the best I’ve ever had. The original and chattahoochie fried chicken were crunchy, juicy, and delicious. Great kids menu. Decent wine menu and great service!😁
First night here with friends out on the deck. Great atmosphere!
